#To enable forward link access in appserver do the following:

vi /var/opt/sun/appserver/domains/domain1/config/domain.xml
#add the following line as shown below for http-listener:
property name="allowLinking" value="true"
virtual-server>
#restart the appserver.
#now you can create any soft link in docroot directory to any other directory , and access it through the browser.
#For eg: ln -s /space/src /var/opt/sun/appserver/domains/domain1/docroot/src
#Now you can access all the contents of src directory throught http://bakhru.red.iplanet.com:8080/src

#Cross-domain communication between two mail-servers
#To achieve the same, you need to setup a local-dns server with proper MX record indicating which mail-server corresponds to which particular domain. On how to do DNS Setup & more details about MX (Mail Exchange) record see here :
#Wikipedia , http://rscott.org/dns/mx.html, http://rscott.org/dns/

To disable recipient address check while sending mail through SMTP server, 
add the keyword 'daemon' in tcp_local channel.

