#Create a filter_discard channel
#Add the following lines in imta.cnf file:
! In rewrite rules section
! filter_discard
.filter_discard-daemon $U%$H.filter_discard@filter_discard-daemon
! In channel defination section
! Filter_discard
filter_discard notices 7 master_debug slave_debug
filter_discard-daemon

########To enable return_job debugging####################
#Edit option.dat file & add the following :
FILTER_DISCARD=2
filter_debug=1
return_debug=1
/opt/sun/comms/messaging64/sbin/configutil |grep schedule
local.schedule.return_job = "30 0 * * * lib/return_job"
local.schedule.return_job.enable = 1


#To change the timezone of a solaris 10 machine, do the following:
edit the /etc/default/init file & change the TZ variable to US/Pacific or any other timezone. ( other timezone examples are availbale at /usr/share/lib/zoneinfo/*) now reboot the machine to have the new timezone.

################# SMTP RELAY SETUP ############################
Installing MS in 2tier mode, front end with MMP & MTA & backend with store,MTA, webmail etc

- Am using two machines here, belugie.red.iplanet.com(backend) & greenmeadow.red.iplanet.com (frontend)
- Install & configure DS, MS,CS,UWC, App/Web server, DA on belugie (backend)
- While configuring MS on belugie, select ALL except MMP.
- Install only MS on greenmeadow.(frontend)
- While configuring MS on greenmeadow, select MTA & MMP (multiplexor)only.
- On backend machine, open the file mappings & edit the following section:
INTERNAL_IP:
- before last line * $N add this , the IP address of greenmeadow.red.iplanet for setting up SMTP relay.
192.18.75.9 $Y
- Check whether you have proper /etc/nsswitch.conf, /etc/hosts, /etc/resolv.conf files. & address resolution (nslookup between frontend & backend is happening properly.
- To verify if everything is working fine, between frontend & backend, run the below command without any failure:
  /opt/SUNWmsgsr/bin/imsimta test -rewrite trin15000@red.iplanet.com

- Done
##################################################################

################# DELETE all mails for a specific user ##############
/opt/sun/comms/messaging64/sbin/mboxutil -d user/$user/INBOX
/opt/sun/comms/messaging64/sbin/mboxutil -d -P '\S*'
##################################################################

### TO SET TIME using TIME SERVER ####
/usr/sbin/ntpdate -s -b -p 8 -u whq4op3u33-rtr-1.us.oracle.com
##############################################################

## TO get msconfig HELP ### equivalent of configutil -H
msconfig help option sslv3enable
